Basically you'll notice that when I was comfortable with giving this restaurant 4 stars about 1.5 years ago, the situation wasn't different from today. The restaurant owner can barely be seen and the maid is running the show. Basically since the half Moroccan half Puerto Rican maid left, some Arab girl has taken care of the show and sucks. First off they take their time bringing the order, everything is overpriced and downsized from 1.5 years ago, 6 dollars for an 8 ounce crappy bannana milkshake, which is listed as 5 dollars in the book (they wouldn't agree to change the price despite this), and when the server brought back my $3 of change, she didn't even wait  to hear my answer to her question about keeping the change for tip, and assumed she could simply pocket it. Ridiculous. Stay away. I am driving in from NJ and would rather going to Ali Baba's
